==Latin==
===Adjective Suffix===
'''-abilis'''

Third declension

# able; adjective suffix generally appended to verbs, usually in a passive sense, forming adjectives meaning "able to be..."
#: amare - amabilis
#: frangere - frangibilis
#: vocare - vocabilis

====Usage Note====
''-abilis'' is usually appended to first conjugation verbs.  Other conjugations use the form '''[[-ibilis]]''' with the same meaning.

